###2026.03.18.05
- Fix: Removed compact-mobile inline order buttons and routed row reordering through quick actions to eliminate persistent iPhone button-box artifacts.
- UX: Reduced mobile 3-dot control size and constrained quick-actions modal to viewport-safe dimensions to prevent top/bottom clipping on phones.


###2026.03.18.04
- Fix: Forced compact mobile settings order and overflow controls to borderless icon buttons so inherited browser button chrome cannot paint box artifacts.
- UX: Removed pseudo/button chrome fallback paths for row controls in mobile settings to avoid duplicate-outline rendering on iPhone Safari.


###2026.03.18.03
- Fix: Added mobile-only hard reset for settings row/action buttons to neutralize browser/theme button overlays that can draw ghost boxes.
- UX: Disabled pseudo-element paint paths on compact settings controls to prevent duplicate border artifacts on touch devices.


###2026.03.18.02
- Fix: Stopped rendering tree-move order buttons in compact mobile settings rows to remove residual ghost button artifacts.
- UX: Added fallback hard-collapse rules for hidden mobile tree-action buttons so Safari/Android cannot paint stray button outlines.


###2026.03.18.01
- Fix: Eliminated mobile settings action-button ghost boxes by hard-collapsing hidden controls in compact table mode.
- UX: Normalized touch focus behavior to prevent persistent outline artifacts around order/actions and bottom action-bar buttons on mobile.


###2026.03.17.28
- Fix: Increased Docker mobile Application-column width allocation so folder names are less aggressively truncated.
- UX: Relaxed Docker mobile text-width caps so longer folder names render before ellipsis while preserving Version-column clearance.


###2026.03.17.27
- UX: Made Docker runtime application sizing deterministic to stop long-name flicker between truncated and expanded states.
- Fix: Enforced bounded Application-Version gap and right-side chevron padding so the compact dropdown icon no longer clips the Version column.
- Performance: Debounced runtime width reflow to recompute only on real layout events including render, resize, font-load, folder-toggle, and prefs updates.
- Test: Expanded browser smoke/runtime checks and CI workflow guards to validate shortest and longest row spacing with failure artifacts.
- Maintenance: Hardened release-note automation fallback so placeholder text cannot ship in new CHANGES entries.


###2026.03.17.26
- Fix: Reduced oversized Application-to-Version spacing by capping overflow nudges used for Docker runtime auto-width correction.
- Fix: Ignored unreliable overflow samples from near-zero label widths during transient render states to prevent accidental column inflation.
- Fix: Bounded mode-stabilized width floor with estimated-width headroom so long-name protection remains without creating large persistent gaps.
- Test: Expanded Docker runtime auto-width regression assertions for bounded overflow and floor-limit behavior.


###2026.03.17.25
- Fix: Eliminated Docker Application-column width thrashing that caused long names to flip between visible and truncated on refresh cycles.
- Fix: Added mode-aware width floor stabilization so overflow-driven expansion persists instead of collapsing on the next auto-size pass.
- Test: Added regression coverage for stabilized Docker auto-width behavior in runtime performance guards.


###2026.03.17.24
- Fix: Docker runtime app column now performs a rendered-overflow pass and expands only when folder names are actually clipped.
- Fix: Long folder names remain fully visible in normal cases without globally widening the Application column.
- Test: Added regression assertions for overflow-aware width adjustment (`scrollWidth`/`clientWidth`) in Docker runtime sizing.


###2026.03.17.23
- Fix: Repositioned Docker folder dropdown chevrons with extra right-side gutter spacing while keeping the button icon-sized to prevent Version-column clipping.
- Feature: Added shared `runtime.column-layout.js` so Docker and VM runtimes use one auto-width/preset/CSS-var column layout engine.
- Feature: Added a dedicated update helper module and new Settings action to generate force-refresh install commands for Unraid cache-bypass updates.
- Quality: Added strict folder/prefs payload-shape validation at server boundaries, including explicit JSON-object enforcement for prefs writes.
- Test: Extended browser smoke checks to validate Docker/VM runtime dropdown overlap metrics and capture artifacts per browser/runtime target.
- Quality: Updated guard scripts so `server/lib*.php` helper modules are treated as libraries instead of mutating endpoints.


